AUDIO: 'Okay. And last year it was a local downloadable app, but now everything runs on your web browser. So you don\'t have to download anything. You can do all relighting that you want to do in your web browser. Okay, that\'s awesome. So yeah, let\'s see how this works. Yeah,'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'so just go to bble.ai and what you do is let\'s say you have a green screen footage. Okay, and what we do is we let you change the lighting on this green screen footage because when you composite with a new background and when'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the lighting doesn\'t match, it can look really bad if the lighting is bad. But now you have the ability to fix that in the post. Mhm. So when you upload it, this is about 15 second of footage and our AI will automatically generate alpha'

[01:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'map to remove the background and also generate all sorts of VFX passes to relight you in the post. So this is your AI model that\'s analyzing this. This is completely the our AI model. Okay. So'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'base color map is kind of removing the existing lighting source. So it\'s removing the green spill, it\'s removing the shadow and so on. Normal map shows you what the geometry is of your subject so that when we cast the light, we can'

[01:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'physically calculate how the shadow should be in the real world. And like roughness map tells you how rough or smooth your texture is. So that smooth parts will have like specular reflections when there\'s point light'

[01:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'added later. So you can you don\'t have to know all these passes, but what you can do is just go to our editor and now it\'s completely black because there\'s no light. But now I can add a light and relight this footage in the post.'

[01:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So And the video is playing back while you\'re relighting too. Yes, exactly. So it\'s very very fast and very light. You can just, you know, increase the intensity. You can change the color of'

